features: [Space-Saving for Any Room] This 11.8"D x 15.7"W x 73.8"H narrow bookshelf occupies little floor space yet offers you 6 tiers of vertical storage, making full use of the small spaces in your living room, bedroom, bathroom, or entryway
[Built to Last] A smart mix of quality particleboard and a sturdy steel frame allows this robust 6-tier bookcase to hold up to 110 lb, giving your items reliable support for years to come
[Easy Assembly] With easy-to-follow instructions and labeled parts for easier understanding, you'll spend less time assembling this display shelf than deciding which book to start reading!

[Stable and Safe] X-shaped bars reinforce the structure, adjustable feet keep this tall book shelf balanced on slightly uneven floors, and the included anti-tip kit will help you fix it to the wall for greater stability and safety

[Embrace an Industrial Vibe] The ebony black shelves paired with a black steel frame create a stylish industrial look, allowing this freestanding shelf to fit seamlessly in with your home decor and give your space an instant update

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great shelf for my needs
reviews.reviewText: Easy to put together. Looks great. Extra parts. Great function. Good value

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this for my wife for our Master Bath, and it's excellent! It's attractive and sturdy. It is easy to assemble with simple instructions, and the feet are adjustable to adjust to any floor or surface.We couldn't be happier with this piece!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great product for the price
reviews.reviewText: I put this shelf together myself in about half an hour. Very simple to assemble and quite sturdy. I like that there are adjustable feet on the bottom in case the floor isn't level. I use it to hold many house plants and a stack of books, and it looks great! Definitely recommend if you need a small shelf and are on a budget.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love this shelf so much. It matches another one I have that’s bigger. My only complaint is there are no bars on the sides to keep books held up so I have to keep them completely in the front or completely in the back and use the posts as makeshift book ends. Other than that, I love this. It was easy to put together and so aesthetically pleasing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Vasagle for the win!
reviews.reviewText: I’ve bought quite a few pieces of Vasagle furniture and they never disappoint. Hands down, they have the easiest instructions to follow. They give you extra screws and all parts are clearly labeled and organized. The packaging is also very good.The shelf itself is very sturdy and nice looking! My daughter is using this for displaying her Funko Pop collection. :-)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023

I also bought a matching desk by the same company and am equally pleased with it.

reviews.reviewTitle: Good quality, and easy to assemble
reviews.reviewText: I do wish there was a slightly lighter colour available, but given the price point its hard to find alternatives that have similar dimensions to this.

Super easy to assemble. The feel of it is leagues better than the usual ikea-type stuff, and while real wood would be heavier duty, this is definitely no slouch. Bought the narrowest one for next to my desk, and I've liked it enough I'm buying three more for other corners of the house. The literal only downside is the stickers they use to ID pieces don't peel off super cleanly, so make sure the side of the shelf with the sticker is hidden (either by books or by facing it down on a lower shelf!) You'll also for sure need bookends due to the lack of enclosure on the sides, but that's hardly the end of the world.
